  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Prompt access to care and treatment adherence are the hearth of tuberculosis control.

      This is a multicentre observational prospective study aimed at studying the factors
      associated with delayed access to care and low adherence to anti-tuberculosis treatment.
      Hetero- and self-administered questionnaires will be used at enrollment to assess clinical
      presentation and time and modalities of the diagnosis. Treatment adherence will be assessed
      during the follow-up with self administered questionnaires.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
